        <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"NewsArticle","mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-syndicate-season-recap"},"headline":"Syndicate 2018 Mega Recap","datePublished":"2018-Sep-Sun","publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Santa Cruz Bicycles","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/sites/all/themes/scb2017/assets/img/ref.svg#santa-cruz-logo"}},"description":"The end is here.Holster your magnums of champagne and deflate the t-rex. World Cup DH is over for the season.The good news is, the Dinoshaw, Slow Loris, and the G.O.A.T are all still here in the archives. For everyone who's looking to kill some time, relive the glory days, and chase the Syndicate around the world one last time, we're dropping some heat.We gathered up each of the news recaps from every race of the season, tossed in a gif or two, and capped the whole thing off with a Syndicate Series playlist and a helmet cam/track preview playlist.Sorry, there's no link to a browser mode that makes this business look like the excel sheet you should be working on ... or instructions to the ride you should be wrenching. We'll Matrix that next time around. Hold on to 'yer butts. Round 1 - Losinj, Croatia[[{\"fid\":\"8357\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"8\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"title\":\"Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"8\"}}]]\"Fresh off early-season training at an undisclosed location (that you might recognize), Greg, Luca, Loris, and team mechanics Doug Hatfield, Jason Marsh, and PA set their sights on the coastal city of Lo\u0161inj, Croatia for the opening round of 2018's World Cup DH season.\"See photos & recap > Round 2 - Fort William, UK[[{\"fid\":\"8397\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate's Loris Vergier Takes Second at the Fort William World Cup\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Loris Takes Second and He Couldn't Be More Stoked\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"9\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate's Loris Vergier Takes Second at the Fort William World Cup\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Loris Takes Second and He Couldn't Be More Stoked\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate's Loris Vergier Takes Second at the Fort William World Cup\",\"title\":\"Loris Takes Second and He Couldn't Be More Stoked\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"9\"}}]]\"Before the first bike hit the Highlands dirt, the news started to fly. The Syndicate\u2019s prototype V10 lit up the Internet, Greg announced that he would be out of the race due to injury and, with the seven-time Fort William winner out of the lineup, speculation flew about who was going to take the lead. The young guns of the Syndicate would have to step up.\"See photos & recap > Round 3 - Leogang, Austria[[{\"fid\":\"8497\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Luca Shaw in the booters on the World Cup DH track at Leogang, Austrai\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Luca Shaw testing the booters at Leogang\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"6\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Luca Shaw in the booters on the World Cup DH track at Leogang, Austrai\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Luca Shaw testing the booters at Leogang\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Luca Shaw in the booters on the World Cup DH track at Leogang, Austrai\",\"title\":\"Luca Shaw testing the booters at Leogang\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"6\"}}]]\"A week after Fort William and we\u2019re racing again, this time in Austria on a track with far less rocks than the previous two rounds. The track in Leogang is known to be one of the fastest on the World Cup circuit.\"See photos & recap > Round 3 - Val di Sole, Italy[[{\"fid\":\"8990\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at Val di Sole World Cup DH - Dougy Fresh\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Dougy Fresh\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"7\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at Val di Sole World Cup DH - Dougy Fresh\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Dougy Fresh\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at Val di Sole World Cup DH - Dougy Fresh\",\"title\":\"Dougy Fresh\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"7\"}}]]\"Round 4 landed in Val di Sole, Italy this year, and, even in good conditions, this is a track with a reputation. It\u2019s rocky and rough from top to bottom and steep as hell throughout.\"See photos & recap > Round 4 - Vallnord, Andorra[[{\"fid\":\"9056\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at World Cup 5 at Andorra\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Champagne for My Real Friends\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"4\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at World Cup 5 at Andorra\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Champagne for My Real Friends\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at World Cup 5 at Andorra\",\"title\":\"Champagne for My Real Friends\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"4\"}}]]\"Loris now takes over the number 2 spot in the World Cup overall standings as we head to Mont Sainte Anne.\"See photos & recap > Round 5 - Mont Sainte Anne[[{\"fid\":\"9377\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Mont Sainte Anne - 2018\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Luca Shaw on pace at MSA 2018\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"3\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Mont Sainte Anne - 2018\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Luca Shaw on pace at MSA 2018\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Mont Sainte Anne - 2018\",\"title\":\"Luca Shaw on pace at MSA 2018\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"3\"}}]]\"The Syndicate would return to Mont Sainte Anne with a full squad and Greg would be making his 20th appearance.\"See photos & recap > Round 6 - La Bresse, France[[{\"fid\":\"9533\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles -  La Bresse - 2018\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Loris Vergier at La Bresse. \",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"2\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles -  La Bresse - 2018\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Loris Vergier at La Bresse. \",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles -  La Bresse - 2018\",\"title\":\"Loris Vergier at La Bresse. \",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"2\"}}]]\"La Bresse is the last regular season race of the year before World Champs in Lenzerheide. \"See photos & recap > World Champs - Lenzerheide[[{\"fid\":\"9665\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":false,\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"1\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":false,\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"1\"}}]]\"The race for the rainbows brought us to Lenzerheide, Switzerland this past weekend. One of the most scenic backdrops on the World Cup circuit, this track features fast and technical terrain with a mix of sniper roots, drops, and rock gardens to challenge racers in the hunt for the coveted rainbow jersey.\"See photos & recap > All the episodes of the Syndicate Series Smashing turns POV-style with helmet cams from the 2018 seasonDo you even follow the @scyndicate on the 'gram? #lightbro","articleBody":"<p>The end is here.</p><p>Holster your magnums of champagne and deflate the t-rex.&nbsp;World Cup DH is over for the season.</p><p>The good news is, the Dinoshaw, Slow Loris, and the G.O.A.T are all still here in the archives.&nbsp;For everyone who's looking to kill some time, relive the glory days, and chase the Syndicate around the world one last time, we're dropping some heat.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" class=\"giphy-embed\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"263\" src=\"https://giphy.com/embed/1Ya1lPdmp1WEHzN9Kc\" width=\"480\"></iframe></p><p>We gathered up each of the news recaps from every race of the season, tossed in a gif or two,&nbsp;and capped the whole thing off with a Syndicate Series playlist and a helmet cam/track preview playlist.</p><p>Sorry, there's no link to a browser mode that makes this business look like the excel sheet you should be working on ... or instructions to the ride you should be wrenching. We'll Matrix that next time around. Hold on to 'yer butts.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Round 1 - Losinj, Croatia</strong></h3><p>[[{\"fid\":\"8357\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"8\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"title\":\"Greg Minnaar Racing World Cup on Reserve Wheels with Chris King Hubs\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"8\"}}]]</p><p><em>\"Fresh off early-season training at an undisclosed location (that you might recognize), Greg, Luca, Loris, and team mechanics Doug Hatfield, Jason Marsh, and PA&nbsp;set their sights on the coastal city of&nbsp;Lo\u0161inj, Croatia&nbsp;for the opening round of 2018's World Cup DH season.\"</em></p><p><strong><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-syndicate-losinj-croatia\"><em>See photos &amp; recap &gt;</em></a></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><b>Round 2 - Fort William, UK</b></h3><p>[[{\"fid\":\"8397\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate's Loris Vergier Takes Second at the Fort William World Cup\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Loris Takes Second and He Couldn't Be More Stoked\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"9\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate's Loris Vergier Takes Second at the Fort William World Cup\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Loris Takes Second and He Couldn't Be More Stoked\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate's Loris Vergier Takes Second at the Fort William World Cup\",\"title\":\"Loris Takes Second and He Couldn't Be More Stoked\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"9\"}}]]</p><p><em>\"Before the first bike hit the Highlands dirt, the news started to fly. The Syndicate\u2019s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.pinkbike.com/news/santa-cruzs-new-v10.html\">prototype V10 lit up the Internet,</a> Greg announced that he would be out of the race due to injury&nbsp;and, with the seven-time Fort William winner out of the lineup, speculation flew about who was going to take the lead. The young guns of the Syndicate would have to step up.\"</em></p><p><strong><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-syndicate-world-cup-fort-william\"><em>See photos &amp; recap &gt;</em></a></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Round 3&nbsp;- Leogang, Austria</strong></h3><p>[[{\"fid\":\"8497\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Luca Shaw in the booters on the World Cup DH track at Leogang, Austrai\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Luca Shaw testing the booters at Leogang\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"6\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Luca Shaw in the booters on the World Cup DH track at Leogang, Austrai\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Luca Shaw testing the booters at Leogang\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Luca Shaw in the booters on the World Cup DH track at Leogang, Austrai\",\"title\":\"Luca Shaw testing the booters at Leogang\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"6\"}}]]</p><p><em>\"A week after Fort William and we\u2019re racing again, this time in Austria on a track with far less rocks than the previous two&nbsp;rounds. The track in Leogang is known to be one of the fastest on the World Cup circuit.\"</em></p><p><strong><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-syndicate-world-cup-leogang\"><em>See photos &amp; recap &gt;</em></a></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Round 3 - Val di Sole, Italy</strong></h3><p>[[{\"fid\":\"8990\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at Val di Sole World Cup DH - Dougy Fresh\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Dougy Fresh\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"7\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at Val di Sole World Cup DH - Dougy Fresh\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Dougy Fresh\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at Val di Sole World Cup DH - Dougy Fresh\",\"title\":\"Dougy Fresh\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"7\"}}]]</p><p><em>\"Round 4 landed in Val di Sole, Italy this year, and, even in good conditions, this is a track with a reputation. It\u2019s rocky and rough from top to bottom and steep as hell throughout.\"</em></p><p><strong><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-world-cup-val-di-sole-italy\"><em>See photos &amp; recap &gt;</em></a></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Round 4 - Vallnord, Andorra</strong></h3><p>[[{\"fid\":\"9056\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at World Cup 5 at Andorra\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Champagne for My Real Friends\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"4\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at World Cup 5 at Andorra\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Champagne for My Real Friends\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - The Syndicate at World Cup 5 at Andorra\",\"title\":\"Champagne for My Real Friends\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"4\"}}]]</p><p><em>\"Loris now takes over the number 2 spot&nbsp;in the World Cup overall standings as we head to Mont Sainte Anne.\"</em></p><p><strong><em><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-world-cup-vallnord-andorra\">See photos &amp; recap &gt;</a></em></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Round 5 - Mont Sainte Anne</strong></h3><p>[[{\"fid\":\"9377\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Mont Sainte Anne - 2018\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Luca Shaw on pace at MSA 2018\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"3\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Mont Sainte Anne - 2018\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Luca Shaw on pace at MSA 2018\",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles - Mont Sainte Anne - 2018\",\"title\":\"Luca Shaw on pace at MSA 2018\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"3\"}}]]</p><p><em>\"The Syndicate would return to Mont Sainte Anne&nbsp;with a full squad and Greg&nbsp;would be making his 20th appearance.\"</em></p><p><strong><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-world-cup-mont-sainte-anne\"><em>See photos &amp; recap &gt;</em></a></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><strong>Round 6 - La Bresse, France</strong></h3><p>[[{\"fid\":\"9533\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles -  La Bresse - 2018\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Loris Vergier at La Bresse. \",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"2\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles -  La Bresse - 2018\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":\"Loris Vergier at La Bresse. \",\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles -  La Bresse - 2018\",\"title\":\"Loris Vergier at La Bresse. \",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"2\"}}]]</p><p><em>\"La Bresse is the last regular season race of the year before World Champs in Lenzerheide. \"</em></p><p><strong><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-world-cup-labresse\"><em>See photos &amp; recap &gt;</em></a></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><h3><b>World Champs - Lenzerheide</b></h3><div><p>[[{\"fid\":\"9665\",\"view_mode\":\"default\",\"fields\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":false,\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"},\"link_text\":null,\"type\":\"media\",\"field_deltas\":{\"1\":{\"format\":\"default\",\"field_file_image_alt_text[en][0][value]\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles\",\"field_file_image_title_text[en][0][value]\":false,\"field_img_caption[und][0][value]\":\"Sven Martin\"}},\"attributes\":{\"alt\":\"Santa Cruz Bicycles\",\"class\":\"media-element file-default\",\"data-delta\":\"1\"}}]]</p></div><p><em>\"The race for the rainbows brought us to Lenzerheide, Switzerland this past weekend.&nbsp;One of the most scenic backdrops on the World Cup circuit, this track features fast and technical terrain with a mix of sniper roots, drops, and rock gardens to challenge racers in the hunt for the coveted rainbow jersey.\"</em></p><p><strong><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-US/news/2018-world-champs-lenzerheide\"><em>See photos &amp; recap &gt;</em></a></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><a id=\"syndicate-series\" name=\"syndicate-series\"></a>All the episodes of the Syndicate Series</strong></p><p><iframe allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?list=PLKBmmHsu3RhT_GEZuJ2jAiXGgkWUAq5HM\" width=\"560\"></iframe></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><a id=\"helmet-cams\" name=\"helmet-cams\"></a>Smashing turns POV-style with helmet cams from the 2018 season</strong></p><p><iframe allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/videoseries?list=PLKBmmHsu3RhSUafClnlf70Vxpe388oTjC\" width=\"560\"></iframe></p><p>Do you even follow the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/scsyndicate/\">@scyndicate</a> on the 'gram? #lightbro</p>","image":["https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/files/lenzer18_h1d6800_0.jpg"]}</script>  
